Service improvement: Following our continuous improvement policy, we will be doing an internal maintenance to enable TLS 1.3 by default on Logs Data Platform. The cipher suites supported after this maintenance will be : * TLS 1.2 Cipher Suites: The server accepted the following 3 cipher suites: TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_CHACHA20_POLY1305_SHA256 256 ECDH: X25519 (253 bits) TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_256_GCM_SHA384 256 ECDH: prime256v1 (256 bits) TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_128_GCM_SHA256 128 ECDH: prime256v1 (256 bits) * TLS 1.3 Cipher Suites: TLS_CHACHA20_POLY1305_SHA256 256 ECDH: X25519 (253 bits) TLS_AES_256_GCM_SHA384 256 ECDH: X25519 (253 bits) TLS_AES_128_GCM_SHA256 128 ECDH: X25519 (253 bits)

incident_updates.body:
Some "Essential" plan services with the maintenance scheduled on March 13 faced issue during their migration. For these services, we restored the data from the latest backup done (in average one hour before the application of the maintenance).
Services initially planed to be migrated on March 14 will be rescheduled on the following days.
Sorry for the inconvenience.

Start time : 13/03/2023 01:00 UTC End time : 26/03/2023 23:00 UTC Service impact : No impact is expected for business and enterprise plans, a small downtime may be experienced for essential plans (less than 15mn). Service improvement : Following our continuous improvement policy, we are rolling out an upgrade of our MongoDB offer.
